      "content": "It is completely understandable to feel that way when the novelty fades and only the weight of expectation remains. Sometimes the most profound magic isn't found in new sights, but in the quiet acceptance that the chapter is closed. You don't have to force yourself to find excitement; just letting go of the need to \"see\" anything else is a form of peace in itself. The exhaustion you feel is valid, but it's okay to rest without needing to justify the silence.",
